article.headline: Johnson's 3 at the buzzer lifts Bellarmine past Kennesaw State 96-95 in OT

images.name: Bellarmine wins it with clutch 3 in final second of OT
images.caption: Ben Johnson connects on a 3-pointer in the final second of overtime to give Bellarmine an unlikely overtime victory over Kennesaw State.

article.linkText: Johnson's 3 at the buzzer lifts Bellarmine past Kennesaw State 96-95 in OT
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- — Beh Johnson hit a 3-pointer as time expired in overtime to lift Bellarmine to a 96-95 win over Kennesaw State on Thursday night. Langdon Hatton had 27 points and 12 rebounds for the Knights (6-17, 2-6 Atlantic Sun Conference). Bash Wieland scored 25 points and added seven rebounds. Garrett Tipton was 7 of 13 shooting (3 for 8 from 3-point range) to finish with 19 points. Quincy Adekokoya led the way for the Owls (13-9, 4-4) with 20 points. Demond Robinson added 17 points for Kennesaw State. In addition, Simeon Cottle had 14 points. Both teams next play Saturday. Bellarmine visits Queens and Kennesaw State plays Eastern Kentucky at home. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
